model.name: vonDassow2000 - Segment Polarity Network model on 1x4 grid of cells

body.p: This is the segment polarity network model described by von Dassow et al. (2000). It represents a toroidal hexagonal array of cells (1x4), where each cell can express various genes (wingless engrailed, hedgehog, cubitus interruptus, and patched) and where their protein products interact within a cell, and across neighboring cells.
